DOT


Akinjide Bankole
r@akinjide.me


With this repo and script included, setup local development environment with all the necessary services and is personalised for my own usage; intended to be used to bootstrap new or existing MacOS environment including core services such as git, pip, tmux, vim and zsh. You can use this script however you like.

You will need to clonse this repository [git clone git@github.com:akinjide/dot.git ~/dot] and run either automatic or manual setup.

Automatic Setup (recommended): This script will detect and run automatically. Use [./boot.sh start] or [./boot.sh help]

Manual Setup: Running manually and commands executed assumes you already have neccessary packages installed on your operating system.

pip: copy pip directory, [cp ~/dot/pip ~/.pip]; create a symbolic link from your copied pip directory, [ln -s ~/.pip/pypirc ~/.pypirc] and [ln -s ~/.pip/pip.conf ~/.pip.conf]; edit the .pypirc file, replacing username and add password [vim ~/.pip/pypirc].

